availableLiquidity(address,address,bool).details: This function calculates the available liquidity for a given account in a market.

params.account: Address of the account for which the available liquidity is to be calculated
params.isLong: Boolean indicating if the position to be calculated is long or short

returns._0: The amount of available liquidity in the market denominated in the collateral token of the market

getFundingFee(address,address,bool).details: This function retrieves the funding fee for a specific account's position in a given market.

params.account: The address of the account whose position the funding fee is being retrieved for.
params.isLong: A boolean indicating whether the position is a long position.
params.market: The address of the market in which the position exists.

returns._0: The funding fee associated with the specified position.

getFundingRate(address,bool).details: This function returns the current and cumulative funding rates of a market for a specified type of position.

params._isLong: A boolean flag indicating whether the position type for which to retrieve the funding rates is a long position.
params._market: The address of the market for which to retrieve the funding rates.

returns._0: A tuple containing two int256 values: `nowRate` and `totalRate`. `nowRate` is the current funding rate of the market for the specified position type, calculated using the formula provided by the `getFundingRate()` function of the associated `IFeeRouter` contract. `totalRate` is the cumulative funding rate of the market for the specified position type, calculated using the cumulativeFundingRates() function of the associated `IFeeRouter` contract.

getMarket(address).details: Retrieves information about a market, including its validation parameters, market parameters, and fee parameters.

params._marketAddr: Address of the market to retrieve information about.

returns.feeOuts: Struct containing the fee parameters, such as fee rates and fee precision.
returns.mktOuts: Struct containing the market parameters, such as token digits, fee rates, and order book and position book addresses.
returns.validOuts: Struct containing the validation parameters for the market.

getMarkets().details: This function returns an array of market information, including the market name, address, and whether the market allows opening and closing positions.

returns._outs: An array of structures containing information about each market, including the name, address, and whether opening and closing positions are allowed.

getPositions(address,address).details: This function retrieves the positions of a given account in a market or in all markets if market address is not provided

params.account: Address of the account whose positions are to be retrieved
params.market: Optional address of the market. If provided, retrieves the positions in the specified market. If not provided, retrieves the positions in all markets

returns._positions: Array of `Position.Props` structures representing the positions of the account in the specified market or in all markets

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

isLiquidate(address,address,bool).details: This function checks if an account's position in a market is eligible for liquidation and returns a state code.

params._account: The address of the account whose position will be checked for liquidation eligibility.
params._isLong: A boolean flag indicating whether the position being checked is a long position.
params.market: The address of the market in which the position is held.

returns._state: A uint256 value representing the state code of the liquidation eligibility check.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
